STATE EX REL. EVANS
v.
OHIO ADULT PAROLE AUTH. 2019-0379 Supreme Court of Ohio. June 24, 2019

CASE ANNOUNCEMENT

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSAL

In Mandamus. On motion to dismiss of Scioto County Prosecutor Shane Tieman. Motion denied on the authority of State ex rel. Evans v. Tieman, ___ Ohio St.3d ___, 2019-Ohio-2411, ___ N.E.3d ___. Sua sponte, cause dismissed for failure to state a claim.

On motion to dismiss of Governor Mike DeWine, Ohio Department of Rehabilitation and Correction Director Annette Chambers-Smith, and the Ohio Adult Parole Authority. Motion granted. Cause dismissed.

Relator's "motion for a simple order that respondents comply and enter the 50 page exhibit into realtor's records" denied.
